$ /boot

The `/boot` directory contains the → Linux/kernel, the → Linux/kernel/initial-ram-disk[ramdisk images], → development/boot-loader[the bootloader configuration file] and the bootloader stages.

This directory is only used during the → Linux/booting[boot process].

sa:
  `→ Linux/fhs/boot/efi`

  `→ Linux/fhs/boot/grub`
